{
  "texts": [
    "The large model CodeGen [145] is used to complete crossover and mutation in the evolutionary process: in the mutation operation, CodeGen makes subtle modifications to the selected network based on the mutation prompt.",
    "In the crossover operation, CodeGen partially matches the selected multiple networks based on the crossover prompt.",
    "Chen et al.",
    "took a similar approach by using the PALM [4] as the crossover and mutation operators for the NAS task in the evolutionary search process.",
    "Moreover, they further improved the LLM's ability of generating candidate architectures through soft prompt tuning during NAS [125]."
  ]
}